column1: # - R1: DPMBot + DNA insert + dA + DPMTop + DPMBot_common_rc + LigEven + OddTop1 + LigOdd + EvenTop1 + LigEven + OddTop2 + LigOdd + EvenTop2 + LigEven + OddTop3 + LigOdd + NYLigOddStgTop + Illumina read 2 sequencing primer_rc
# - R2: NYStgBot + Odd + OddBot3 + Even + EvenBot2 + Odd + OddBot2 + Even + EvenBot1 + Odd + OddBot1 + Even + DPMBot_common + DPMBot + DNA insert + dA + DPMTop + Illumina read 1 sequencing primer_rc
# - 5' processing: identify and trim 5' DPM from R1; identify and trim 5' barcode from R2
#   - R2: dA + DPMTop (unique) + Rd1Sp = dA + DPMTop

#   - Below, I include each DPM tag 4 times: R1 without indels, R2 without indels, R1 allowing indels (but remove 1 nt from start of tag sequence so that that tag won't "eat" into actual DNA insert), R2 allowing indels
# - Filter for reads with at least 20 bp genomic DNA remaining after trimming barcodes.

# - This config assumes that all 96 tags are used in each round. Tags that were not actually used may lead to false positive clusters, although oligos containing these tags would likely end up in unassigned clusters (e.g., none, ambiguous, uncertain).
# - The edit distances here are appropriate if all 96 tags are used in each round; more flexible edit distances may be allowed if only a subset of tags are used in each round.
# - The DPM_const tag does not allow indels to prevent the tag from consuming any bases that actually correspond to the subsequent DPM_R2 tag.

# - Read lengths of 10 x 165 are required to span (assuming no indels) the 5' barcode sequences shown in the structures above. To sequence 20 nt of genomic DNA ("DNA insert") in each read orientation, read lengths should be >= 30 x 185.

# - For performance reasons, the 3' trimming tags are limited to a maximum 30 nt length and 1 edit distance (Hamming or Levenshtein). Allowing a Hamming distance of 2 already significantly increases runtime and memory usage; allowing partial3 error rate of 3/30 or greater is not practical.
# Splitcode command: splitcode -c config.tsv --nFastqs=2 --assign --mod-names --mapping=/dev/null --no-outb --output=output_R1.fastq.gz,output_R2.fastq.gz input_R1.fastq.gz input_R2.fastq.gz
